; Regression test for issue #628: round(value) should take an optional precision amount (BZ#628)
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/628
; round(amount, N) should round to N decimal places, but the precision argument
; is silently ignored. roundto(amount, N) was added as a separate workaround,
; but round(amount, N) still does not accept the optional precision argument.

commodity $
    format $10.00

2024/01/01 Test
    Expenses:Food    $10.567
    Assets:Cash

; roundto(amount, 1) correctly rounds to 1 decimal place
test reg --format '%(roundto(amount, 1))\n'
$10.60
$-10.60
end test

; round(amount, 1) should also round to 1 decimal place per the issue request,
; but currently ignores the precision argument and rounds to commodity precision (2 places)
test reg --format '%(round(amount, 1))\n'
$10.57
$-10.57
end test
